CUPP
Common User Passwords Profiler

Password Attacks
Description
CUPP creates custom wordlists based on target personal information like names, birthdays, pets, etc. Generates targeted password lists for social engineering.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

ls cupp.py
Install command:

git clone https://github.com/Mebus/cupp.git
Basic Syntax
python3 cupp.py -i
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
python3 cupp.py -i

Interactive mode	Create custom wordlist	
python3 cupp.py -w

Improve existing list	Add permutations	
python3 cupp.py -l

Download wordlists	Get common lists	
python3 cupp.py -a

Default Alecto DB	Use default credentials	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Gather target personal info
2
Run CUPP in interactive mode
3
Enter names, dates, keywords
4
Review generated wordlist
5
Use with hydra/medusa
Understanding the Output
Creates a text file with password combinations based on provided info.

